articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Workers and activists across Europe plan demonstrations against U.S. e-commerce giant Amazon on Friday, aiming to disrupt its warehouses and prevent merchandise from reaching Amazon parcel lockers on one of the busiest shopping days of the year.
articles.title: Amazon protests in Europe target warehouses, lockers on busy Black Friday

articles.author: Fanny Potkin, Yelin Mo
articles.description: Nvidia (NVDA.O) has told customers in China it is delaying the launch of a new artificial intelligence chip it designed to comply with U.S. export rules until the first quarter of next year, two sources familiar with the matter said.
articles.title: Exclusive: Nvidia delays launch of new China-focused AI chip -sources

articles.author: Nivedita Balu
articles.description: The Bank of Canada's warning that borrowing costs are likely to stay higher-for-longer has prompted anxious mortgage owners to turn to fixed-rate loans in the hope they will bring more stability to their finances after a choppy few years.
articles.title: Canadian homeowners eye fixed-rate loans in 'higher-for-longer' era

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Tesla (TSLA.O) is ready to invest up to $2 billion to set up a factory in India if the government cuts import duty on its vehicles to 15% for the first two years of operations, the Economic Times reported on Friday.
articles.title: Tesla ready to invest up to $2 bln to build India factory, but with riders -ET

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Germany's economy shrank slightly in the third quarter compared with the previous three months, data from its statistics office showed on Friday.
articles.title: Germany's economy shrinks slightly in third quarter

articles.author: Katherine Masters
articles.description: Retailers are hoping forecasts for a cool, dry Black Friday across much of the U.S. will drive millions of shoppers to their stores in the kickoff to the key holiday shopping season.
articles.title: US retailers hope to draw picky Black Friday shoppers to stores

articles.author: Nick Carey
articles.description: Nissan (7201.T) said on Friday it will invest 1.12 billion pounds ($1.4 billion) to build electric versions of two popular crossover models at its UK plant in a fresh boost for Britain's auto industry amid the switch to electric vehicles.
articles.title: Nissan to invest $1.4 bln to build two new EV models in Britain

articles.author: Andrew Mills, Bassam Masoud
articles.description: Israel and Hamas start a four-day truce on Friday morning with the militants to release a first group of 13 Israeli women and child hostages later in the day, the first break in a war that has devastated the besieged Gaza enclave.
articles.title: Israel, Hamas to start first truce in Gaza war

articles.author: Yimou Lee, Sarah Wu
articles.description: Taiwan's opposition parties, which seek closer China ties, registered separate presidential candidates on Friday after a dramatic split, potentially easing the way for the ruling party, which has defied Beijing's pressure, to stay in power.
articles.title: China ties on the line as Taiwan opposition splits in dramatic feud

articles.author: Andrew Silver, Nicoco Chan
articles.description: China called for vigilance on Friday as a surge of respiratory illness hit schools and hospitals and the World Health Organization, which has asked the government for disease data, said no unusual or novel pathogens had been detected.
articles.title: China grapples with respiratory illness spike; WHO says no unusual pathogen found
